tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows borderline elevated HbA1c, suggesting possible impaired glucose tolerance. Lipid profile reveals high total and LDL cholesterol, low HDL, and normal triglycerides, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. Mildly decreased total CO₂ may suggest a mild metabolic acidosis or compensated respiratory alkalosis. Renal function, electrolytes, and glucose are within normal limits. Recommend further cardiovascular risk assessment and consideration of lifestyle or pharmacological interventions.
